verbose_text: ABCA1 and ABCG1, membrane transporters abundant in macrophages, mediate the efflux of cholesterol and phospholipids to lipid-free apolipoproteins (apoA1 and apoE) to then form nascent high-density lipoprotein (HDL).
evidence: ABCA1 and ABCG1, membrane transporters abundant in macrophages, mediate the efflux of cholesterol
